East African poultry company Kenchic has opened a store in Kiambu town which it says could create as much as 1,500 jobs in the county.&ldquo;Kiambu is one of the best markets for our products and therefore, this facility will create employment to budding poultry farmers whilst boosting poultry production to existing farmers,&rdquo; Kenchic managing director James Oduor said in a statement.The centre in Ikinu-Kiambu which is the eighth of its kind in the country will stock products such as day-old-chicks including broilers, layers and kenbro breed, chicken feed, disinfectants, vaccines and vitamins.